         <abstract>
            <p>The ultraconvergence property of a derivative recovery technique recently proposed by Zienkiewicz and Zhu is analyzed for two-point boundary value problems. Under certain regularity assumptions on the exact solution, it is shown that the convergence rate of the recovered derivative at an internal nodal point is two orders higher than the optimal global convergence rate when even-order finite element spaces and local uniform meshes are used.</p>
          </abstract>
